<tt>Sun Nov 16 14:50:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all of you who are looking for your brothers, Washington, D.C. has a tent in front of the Lincoln Memorial called Friends of the Vietnam Memorial.  They can put the people you are looking for on a list for other Vets to search and find eachother.  They helped me find a Vet who served with my father.  He was a Paratrooper 101st Airborne 1966.  I am sure they can help you find who you are looking for.  Take care and WELCOME HOME.  The daughter of a KIA is proud of all of you.  
<p><code>-- DAWNEE@AOL.COM  (Dawn) </code><p>


